backend/
    The FastAPI backend is vendored from / derived from the upstream
    "HackingPal" project (formerly "MyHackingPal"; the rebrand is still
    visible in the tree — e.g. the "HackingPal"/"MyHackingPal" keychain
    service names in backend/routers/settings.py and the ~/.hackingpal and
    ~/.myhackingpal preset directories in backend/lib/preset_engine.py).

    The routers under backend/routers/ are treated as a vendored snapshot of
    that upstream and are carried largely as-is; local functionality is added
    in separate modules rather than by hand-editing the vendored routers.

    NOTE: backend/UPSTREAM.md, which is expected to record the exact upstream
    provenance and commit, is not present in this tree. Update this NOTICE with
    the precise upstream repository URL, commit/tag, and upstream license once
    that provenance record is added.
